      NOTE: you cannot remake HCE without the Commodore Include files.


      HOW TO MAKE HCE.
      ----------------

      FROM HCE:

      1) Select 'Load (c/a-source)' from the 'Disk' menu and then 
         load this document (if you haven`t already).
         You can then view the instructions from the editor.
      2) Select 'Lock?' from the 'Other' menu and then Lock the
         'HceSrc:HCE/HCE/' directory.
      3) Select 'Compiler-options' from the 'Compile' menu.
      4) Select 'Load Compile List' and load the file called 'HCE.CL'.
      5) Click on the 'Compile' gadget until it shows 'FROM-LIST'.
      6) Exit the options window.
      7) Set the 'Outpath' gadget in the  'Assembler-options' window to
         a path of your choice. (Default is, RAM:)
      8) Select the 'Compile+Optimize+Assemble' gadget.
      9) Wait until all files have been compiled.(30-40 mins)
     10) Lock the 'HceSrc:HCE/HCC/' directory.
     11) Select 'Compiler-options' from the 'Compile' menu.
     12) Select 'Load Compile List' and load the file called 'HCC.CL'.
     13) Exit the options window.
     14) Set the 'Outpath' gadget again.(is changed when list is loaded)
     15) Select the 'Compile+Optimize+Assemble' gadget.
     16) Wait until all files have been compiled.(10-20 mins)
     17) Select 'Linker-options' from the 'Link' menu.
     18) Select 'Load Link List' and load the file called 'HCE.LL' from
         this directory.( HceSrc:HCE/HCE.LL )
     19) If you do not have enough memory then change the 'OutName' gadget
         to a name+path of your choice.
     20) Exit the options window.
     21) Select 'Link List' from the Link menu and wait.(1-2 mins)

